<div class="left-panel-step-3"></div>


<div class="container-fluid custom-container top-margin-adjustment-for-fixed-navbar">
    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-md-3 column-adjustment-step-3 activity-page-left-panel-column-adjustment">
            <div class="activity-page-left-panel-div-block">
                <a href="../step-3" class="activity-page-back-link">&lt; Back</a>
                  <img src="/media/images/beautify-your-yard2x.png" alt="" class="large-icon">
                  <div class="who-its-for-div-block">
                    <img src="/media/images/individual-icon.png" class="small-icon">
                    <div class="who-its-for">Individual</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="time-to-complete-div-block"><img src="/media/images/alarm-clock.png" class="small-icon">
                    <div class="time-to-complete">20 - 30 minutes</div>
                </div>
                <h1 class="activity-page-title">Rate your Household</h1>
                <h2 class="activity-page-question">Why do this?</h2>
                <p class="activity-page-question-answer">To quickly identify different types of "habitats" or
                  surfaces in your neighbourhood.</p>
            </div>
        </div>


        <div class="col-md-9 right-panel-adjustment activity-page-right-panel-column-adjustment">

            <div class="div-block-7">
                <div class="div-block-6">
                    <h3 class="activity-heading-1 heading-color-adjustment">Causes & Mitigation</h3>
                    <p>A higher score indicates a lowercarbon footprint.</p>
                    <br>

                    <h3 class="activity-description heading-color-adjustment">1. How much floor area for heating and cooling per person is in your home?</h3>
                    <form>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="3" checked> < 50 m<sup>2</sup><br>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="2"> 50 - 120 m<sup>2</sup><br>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="1"> > 120 m<sup>2</sup>
                    </form>

                    <h3 class="activity-description heading-color-adjustment">2. How do you heat/cool your home?</h3>
                    <form>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="3" checked> Mostly renewable energy (eg. solar, hydro, air-sourced heat pumps)<br>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="2"> Combination of renewable energy and fossil fuels<br>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="1"> Mostly fossil fuels (eg. natural gas)
                    </form>

                   <h3 class="activity-description heading-color-adjustment">3. Has your home been retrofitted for energy efficiency?</h3>
                   <form>
                     <input type="radio" name="climate" value="3" checked> In the last 10 years<br>
                     <input type="radio" name="climate" value="2"> In the last 20 years<br>
                     <input type="radio" name="climate" value="1"> Over 20 years ago or never
                   </form>

                   <h3 class="activity-description heading-color-adjustment">4. % of your house shaded by trees in your yard or block in summer</h4>
                     <form>
                       <input type="radio" name="climate" value="3" checked> > 60%<br>
                       <input type="radio" name="climate" value="2"> 30 - 60%<br>
                       <input type="radio" name="climate" value="1"> < 30%
                     </form>

                  <h3 class="activity-description heading-color-adjustment">5. % of trips by foot/bike/bus in one week:</h4>
                    <form>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="3" checked> > 60%<br>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="2"> 30 - 60%<br>
                      <input type="radio" name="climate" value="1"> < 30%
                    </form>
                    <br>
                    <a href="../step-3/a1-p2" class="button">Next</a>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

